            <item>
             <widget class="QLabel" name="label_Tips">
              <property name="text">
               <string>&lt;b&gt;Undervolting:&lt;/b&gt; Start with -50mV on core/cache, test stability with stress tests (prime95, stress-ng). Decrease by -10mV increments if unstable. Can reduce temps by 10-15°C.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fan Curves:&lt;/b&gt; Balance noise vs cooling. Typical points: 30°C→30%, 50°C→40%, 70°C→60%, 85°C→80%, 95°C→100%. Ensure monotonic increase (later points ≥ earlier).
&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Power Limits:&lt;/b&gt; Lowering PL1/PL2 reduces heat and noise with minimal performance loss. For gaming: PL1=45W, PL2=65W is good balance. For productivity: PL1=35W, PL2=55W extends battery.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Battery Life:&lt;/b&gt; Quiet mode + disable E-cores on Intel 12th+ + 1.5-2.0 GHz max freq + lower screen brightness = 2-3x runtime.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Thermal Throttling:&lt;/b&gt; If temps hit 100°C, lower PL2, improve cooling (laptop stand, clean fans), or reduce max frequency to 4.0-4.5 GHz.</string>
              </property>
